            "title": "Educa\u00e7\u00e3o de jovens e adultos : diversidade, inclus\u00e3o e conscientiza\u00e7\u00e3o",
            "abstract": [
                "The book \"Education of Youth and Adults: Diversity, inclusion and awareness\" is situated in the context of a multiplicity of training processes aimed at contemplating, in addition to the quest to overcome absolute illiteracy, the debate on themes aimed at broadening the conception of EJA , which, although publicized, are rarely included in the teaching programs of this segment of basic education, such as cultural identity, differences, racial issues, power relations, gender issues, art and popular culture, among others. others, all of them lacking public policies for their implementation. It is understood as imperative the production and dissemination of knowledge involving EJA in order to consolidate it as an effective field of theoretical-practical reflections aimed at guaranteeing access and permanence of subjects in the school environment located in a true mosaic of cultures, ethnicities , living conditions and social groups, with yearnings for social development, constitute an enormous challenge for public policies. Thus, in the set of texts of the work, the theoretical foundation of several curricular components of this area of knowledge, the documentary analysis aimed at legal support and, in particular, proposals for didactic-pedagogical intervention aimed at the necessary mediation for the constitution of public policies and true citizenship education. Thus, the book is of interest for the initial training of teachers, for teachers who teach in EJA and for professionals in education networks involved with technical-pedagogical guidance and initial or continuing training of educators",
                "O livro \u201cEduca\u00e7\u00e3o de Jovens e Adultos: Diversidade, inclus\u00e3o e conscientiza\u00e7\u00e3o\u201d se situa no contexto de uma multiplicidade de processos formativos voltados a contemplar, para al\u00e9m da busca de supera\u00e7\u00e3o do analfabetismo absoluto, o debate sobre tem\u00e1ticas voltadas ao alargamento da concep\u00e7\u00e3o de EJA, as quais, embora propaladas, raramente s\u00e3o consignadas nos programas de ensino desse segmento da educa\u00e7\u00e3o b\u00e1sica tais como a identidade cultural, as diferen\u00e7as, a quest\u00e3o racial, as rela\u00e7\u00f5es de poder, a tem\u00e1tica de g\u00eanero, a arte e a cultura popular, entre outras, todas elas a carecer de pol\u00edticas p\u00fablicas para efetiva\u00e7\u00e3o. Compreende-se como imperativa a produ\u00e7\u00e3o e difus\u00e3o de saberes envolvendo a EJA de modo a consolid\u00e1-la como um campo efetivo de reflex\u00f5es te\u00f3rico-pr\u00e1ticas voltadas \u00e0 garantia do acesso e perman\u00eancia dos sujeitos no ambiente escolar situado em um verdadeiro mosaico de culturas, etnias, condi\u00e7\u00f5es de vida e grupos sociais, com anseios de desenvolvimento social, a constituir enorme desafio para as pol\u00edticas p\u00fablicas. Assim, no conjunto dos textos da obra, destacam-se a fundamenta\u00e7\u00e3o te\u00f3rica de v\u00e1rios componentes curriculares dessa \u00e1rea do conhecimento, a an\u00e1lise documental voltada \u00e0 sustenta\u00e7\u00e3o legal e, em especial, propostas de interven\u00e7\u00e3o did\u00e1tico-pedag\u00f3gica voltadas \u00e0 media\u00e7\u00e3o necess\u00e1ria para a constitui\u00e7\u00e3o de pol\u00edticas p\u00fablicas e verdadeira forma\u00e7\u00e3o cidad\u00e3. Desse modo, o livro \u00e9 de interesse para a forma\u00e7\u00e3o inicial de professores, para docentes que ensinam na EJA e para profissionais das redes de ensino envolvidos com orienta\u00e7\u00e3o t\u00e9cnico-pedag\u00f3gica e forma\u00e7\u00e3o inicial ou continuada 